						<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#330000" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<DIV>I would like to open a constructive dialogue about the new paladin epic(s) 1.5 has been discovered / solved so I would like to stay with that for now, this way nothing can be spoiled.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I would greatly appreciate for Brenlo and perhaps even a Dev to join this dialogue with the paladin community in regards to our new epic weapon. I do not wish this to turn into a class balance issue, so please, do not compare the weapon to weapons of other classes, compare it to the &nbsp;weapon(s) being upgraded.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Also please maintain civility in this thread. Lets try to keep this positive and constructive as it effects the paladin class across the board, both in the now and in the future.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Problem: Many long standing members of the paladin community feel that the present day&nbsp; needs of the&nbsp;Paladin were not taken into consideration when our new epic weapon was designed. For many, a 2 handed weapon simply isnt useable as the hit point and armor class drop to equip the weapon makes it too much of a risk from a defensive standpoint. Many gave input to this fact that a one hand equippable weapon was preferred over a 2 handed weapon, was this input taken into consideration and could we get a reason as to why a 2 hander was chosen despite this input?&nbsp; Can we perhaps have an additional quest to replace the epic with a weapon (1 hander)&nbsp;more of us can use, as an option?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>My thanks in advance, I know Brenlo and the Devs have alot to do, but I feel a dialogue on this issue would be both&nbsp;a positive and appreciated step towards achieving customer satisfaction.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Alvret </DIV>
<DIV>[70 Lord] Tholuxe Paells</DIV>
																		
