									</span>

									<img src='/i/skins/default/icon_rating_5.gif' border=0 alt='1 rating - 5.0 average' width=55 height=10>
									</td>

						<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#330000" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Zajeer-Dev wrote:<BR>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Traditionally knights, up until lately with new shield&nbsp;block&nbsp;AAs, have been driven towards using 2handers for a good majority of their time. As such, it was decided to make the epic a 2hander. Adding in a quest to make the 2hander a 1hander won't be equitable, as every other class will want the same option to swap their weapons. Moreover, the epic itself is built art-wise as a 2hander, and making it a 1hander would not scale correctly.<BR>
<HR>
</DIV></BLOCKQUOTE>
<DIV>This makes me sad to hear. I would be interested in knowing if this really is based on facts or just a general feeling. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>As we all know knights were at their peak of power in PoP. This resulted in people choosing the equipment most suitable at the time and that meant you could maximize your DPS and not bother much about the defensive side, thus use a 2handed weapon.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Noone can possibly&nbsp;have missed the outrage from the players regarding the higher difficulty to tank mobs in GoD leading to several changes to the game.&nbsp;We also did what we could and a LOT of knights adjusted and bagged their 2hander for a shield to help them survive. If you made a comparison today I am sure there is quite a few knights that use 1h+shield but of course if you cont from 1999 "using 2handers for a good majority of their time" will still be true..... </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Then there is also a fact that pre Plane of Time the 1handers and sheilds just isn't good enough compared to for example SEWS or RWM. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>The whole art-wise thing may be an issue for you as a developer but I really think it would had been better to leave that part out since I doubt the customers really want to be reminded technicalities like that are more important than the gameplay, even if I realize it probably is.... But&nbsp;any way... wasn't Ghoulbane a 2handed sword model back in the day and yet wielded in one hand? </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I realize you cannot make exceptions for paladins. I also realize if it was a 1hander people would still have objections. However my main&nbsp;issue is that the call for a 1hander was louder than for a 2hander long before OoW was finished. That should had been a wakeup call regarding what we wanted in the future no matter what we used most of the time in the past.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Also it makes little sense to put defensive abilities on a offensive type of weapon regardless if I can click it from my inventory or not.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
																																		<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 100; overflow: hidden;">
