<DIV>Adding in a quest to make the 2hander a 1hander won't be equitable, as every other class will want the same option to swap their weapons. Moreover, the epic itself is built art-wise as a 2hander, and making it a 1hander would not scale correctly.</DIV><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>I am distressed at this attitude.&nbsp; If so many players are unhappy with the form of their epic, then go ahead make a second version for all the classes.&nbsp; Is this so hard to grasp?&nbsp; Yes, it means more work, but that would seem a pittance in this instance.&nbsp; Artwork?&nbsp; Who's getting the item so they can "look pretty" to others?&nbsp;&nbsp;I would think most people are getting it to have a very nice and usable item in their hand with "prettiness" being a distant secondary concern.</P>
<P>I must agree with Juujuu on this.&nbsp; No additional quest is really needed.&nbsp; The&nbsp;player already did the quest, they just want the item in a different (more usable) form.&nbsp; Hand the NPC the (already received) epic to exchange it for a 1-handed variant.&nbsp; For rangers, hand it back for a bow variant.&nbsp; </P>
<P>This isn't&nbsp;an issue about making the quests longer and harder, it's about getting a different item and that's all.</P>
																		
										</td></tr>
