						<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#330000" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Zajeer-Dev wrote:<BR>
<DIV>Basically, every class is going to have issues with what weapon type their epic is. There are a handful of monks that are not happy with their weapon being hand-to-hand. There are a handful of rangers who are unhappy that their weapon isn't a bow. There are a handful of warriors who would rather have a 2hander. The same can be said for knights with 2handers&nbsp;and 1handers. Had the epic been a 1hander, we would have seen this same post, but by a different poster, stating that they would rather have the epic be a 2hander.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Traditionally knights, up until lately with new shield&nbsp;block&nbsp;AAs, have been driven towards using 2handers for a good majority of their time. As such, it was decided to make the epic a 2hander. Adding in a quest to make the 2hander a 1hander won't be equitable, as every other class will want the same option to swap their weapons. Moreover, the epic itself is built art-wise as a 2hander, and making it a 1hander would not scale correctly.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>After this next live patch, all epics will be usable for inventory. So if you're more of the one-hander type knight, then you can still have some effectiveness out of your epic (by being able to click it from inventory) and still use a 1hander and shield.</DIV><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>I would have to say, that you are not very in touch with the paladin population to make these comments.</P>
<P>The only advantage of 2h weapons over 1h/shield is DPS, and most knights will tell you flat out, DPS is a distant concern to us in comparison to surviving as a tank.&nbsp; I lost 100 ac and 160 hp/mana by equiping the new epic.&nbsp; The HP/mana is one thing, but the additional damage I take with the lower AC is significant and was commented on immediately by a couple of clerics who healed me while I was using it.</P>
<P>When you say 'some people' of various classes are not happy about the choice for their epic, you can not include the paladin class, as from my personal conversations and from what I have seen posted, its a STRONG majority that want the paladin to be a 1h, in fact, its not even close.</P>
<P>Thanx for making it clickable from inventory tho, not a total loss that way.</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>McBash<BR></P>
