			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<DIV>I don't want to divert the topic but I strongly disagree that the majority of paladins wanted their epics in the current form. There were a number of posts discussing the issue and asking that the paladin weapon be 1-handed. Those requests were not granted.&nbsp;That was an SOE decision and not a decision based on the desires of the majority of paladins posting here or at PoN. To claim so is not an accurate representation of the discussions on both of the previously mentioned boards that have occurred ever since the idea of an epic 2 was confirmed. &nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I use one-handed or two-handed weapons as the situation dictates to contribute to the group or raid. If I am tanking, there is a noticable drop in tankability when I switch from 1h to 2h. This is working as intended. 1h is for tanking and 2h is for a marginal increase in dps. Given our principal role is tanking, the epic should have been 1h. To be honest, a transmutable weapon would have been the best solution. Given our request was not granted and folks are upset, you have to decide what to do now. </DIV>
																		
