			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<DIV>Alvret, the 1.5 epic is supposed to be on par with a time level weapon, which means better then elementals. I think this weapon qualifies as better then elemental for sure, therefore it is a time level weapon and is in line with other weapons there. A 2hander and a 1hander+shield can't be compared thus.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Here is my problem, it is a dps weapon with defensive effects and foci. This makes the weapon not only confusing to use but really not very usable. Here are the issues as I see them.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>You wanted to give paladins some tanking help and decided on the epic focus, I love that focus it is awesome. You also knew that we have a ton of AA's specifically for 2handers and knew that a 2hander would be a nice dps upgrade for us in the end. Both of those statements are very true, however in combination they don't work. If you want to give us a dps weapon then please give us effects and foci that are for dps and not for tanking. If you want to help us in tanking then give us the effects and foci for tanking on a tanking weapon.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Persoanlly I think the indviidual two halves of the weapon are awesome. So I would ask that you complete the weapon, either make it a pure dps weapon or a pure tanking weapon. I don't think the way to fix it is to make it usable with the new shield block AA, but it would be a fix. It's just that if we are to use it to taqnk with we loose too many stats, most importantly ac and hp.</DIV>
