						<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#330000" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<DIV></DIV><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Zajeer-Dev wrote:<BR>
<DIV>After this next live patch, all epics will be usable for inventory. 
<HR>
</DIV></BLOCKQUOTE>
<DIV>This sort of problem comes up again and again with items. My understanding is that they made the "must equip" flag because they couldn't do class/race requirement checks on inventory items leading to things like the DE mask that is brd/rog only but clickable by anyone from inventory.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>However, since that problem was fixed, why can't you change ALL items to be clickable from inventory? There are a lot of cases (cleric epic 1.0 is probably the biggest example) where people spend lots of time swapping items in just to click them. This is very annoying to players and accomplishes nothing from a game-balance perspective. Many clerics just wield their epic 1.0 forever because swapping items constantly is such a pain. Many caster/priest classes don't want to give up the click effect on their Time items to wield the new epics.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Ideally, it would be nice if items were hotkeyable and clickable from within bags as well, but making everything clickable from regular inventory slots would be a huge step in the right direction and make&nbsp;a lot of players much happier.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>-Belanar</DIV>
																		
										</td></tr>
