												<br><blockquote><hr>Zajeer-Dev wrote:<br><DIV>Basically, every class is going to have issues with what weapon type their epic is. There are a handful of monks that are not happy with their weapon being hand-to-hand. There are a handful of rangers who are unhappy that their weapon isn't a bow. There are a handful of warriors who would rather have a 2hander. The same can be said for knights with 2handers and 1handers. Had the epic been a 1hander, we would have seen this same post, but by a different poster, stating that they would rather have the epic be a 2hander.</DIV><DIV> </DIV><DIV>Traditionally knights, up until lately with new shield block AAs, have been driven towards using 2handers for a good majority of their time. As such, it was decided to make the epic a 2hander. Adding in a quest to make the 2hander a 1hander won't be equitable, as every other class will want the same option to swap their weapons. Moreover, the epic itself is built art-wise as a 2hander, and making it a 1hander would not scale correctly.</DIV><DIV> </DIV><DIV>After this next live patch, all epics will be usable for inventory. So if you're more of the one-hander type knight, then you can still have some effectiveness out of your epic (by being able to click it from inventory) and still use a 1hander and shield.</DIV><br><hr></blockquote><br><br><br><br>Jaz, you are very out of touch with both knight classes.  SoE created "what do you want as your epic" posts got replies that were largely "we want a 1hander for tanking or a 2hander for dps" not "We want a dps weapon with tanking modifiers".  A 2h epic with no help to +damage is pointless being a 2hander.  Once you reach Time and above, ANY 1hander + shield will outperform this in terms of tanking.  We basically have a DPS weapon with NO built-in help for dps.<br><br>Knights are going ah+shield because thats the way we are forced to tank due to game mechanics.  Nobody has any understanding of why you are making tanking 2handers that are unquestionably worse in shielding, ac, hp, stats, resists and avoidance % than 1handers and told "here, use this for tanking".<br><br>WQe also want to know why it has a mere 25 more hp, 10 more ac, and LESS shielding than the 1handers given to other classes.<br><br>Do you realize how infrequently this will be used by even time (and Ikkinz 3 is doable by a very solid group of pre-time people as well) geared people for what you are intending it to be used for?  <br><br><br>The epic itself is actually designed as a 1.5hander (**SMURF** sword), as its blade and hilt are out of proportion to what a traditional 2handed sword looks like.<br><br>Additionally, I can pretty much assure you that no shaman, druid, cleric, wizard, enchanter, necromancer, mage, berserker or rogue is unhappy with their  epic being a 1hander (or 2hander for zerkers), seeing as how 1handers are by far better as "epic" pieces (or 2handers for zerkers), or as daggers to poke things really hard with.  <br><br>We all know you messed up the design of the Paladin (and likely SK) weapons, we see that every day we log in.  Good focus, good DPS weapon... bad weapon as a whole because of it.  We need this fixed.
