						<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#330000" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>Myanta, I do not believe you understood my point and the question I was asking of Zajeer.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>The epic 1.5 is supposed to be an upgrade to potime weapons in regards to stats, this is fairly consistant throughout their designs. I can indeed compare a 1 handed weapon and shield to a 2 handed weapon as this is entirely the point. Our epic takes up 2 slots and therefore is responsible for providing us stats from 2 slots. The entire point of an epic for many, is to provide a great item (upgrade)&nbsp;for the slot(s) it occupies. Something grand which was achieved with somewhat of a great effort.&nbsp; I am somewhat hindered as the original parameters means we can only factually discuss epic 1.5, but it is no secret epic 2.0 is similar in regards to being a 2 hander with similar effects.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;To gain 260 hp/mana from 2 inventory slots makes it a sub par item when compared with the preferred gear of most paladins.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;To gaina&nbsp; bonus to being healed but loose AC, HP, the ability to gain mitigation&nbsp;with shield block is nearly the same as just cancelling the healing effect. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp; I highly doubt that using a 40 delay 71 damage weapon is enough to turn the paladin into a legitimate dps class, so what is the purpose? This seems much similar to giving a ranger or a rogue a shield. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;I understand our two hander AAs from Planes of power had an influence, but I thought our AAs from Omens of war might have more of an influence on an epic designed with the omens of war expansion.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>There is the idea that epic 1.5 is for the casual player, but by projecting the stats of this epic you could come up with stats of 370 hp / 370 mana (pure speculation)&nbsp;on epic 2.0. Which will also be a downgrade. Should we give up defense and survivability by equipping our best weapon for the class? My point is, this weapon really isnt designed for our class as it exists now and epics are supposed to be class specific.&nbsp;Your thoughts&nbsp;Zajeer? Brenlo? </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Again, these are just questions aimed at having a dialogue about many issues concerned customers have come up with, regarding the new epic. They arent meant to be arguementive in my case, but they are concerns. My thanks for your time, it is appreciated.</DIV>
