			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<DIV>Zajeer,</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I'd like you to consider what you have put to us to explain this situation.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>
<HR>
Traditionally knights, up until lately with new shield&nbsp;block&nbsp;AAs, have been driven towards using 2handers for a good majority of their time. As such, it was decided to make the epic a 2hander.<BR>
<HR>
</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>If this is the case, why were we not given a 1HS epic when apparently you already know that only in the past Paladins used 2HS weapons, but now need 1HS weapons to do their job. You said it yourself, "up until lately" so I ask why are we in this situation at all?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>
<DIV>The developers have created this problem by ignoring the community, and with seemingly no good reason for it. I don't see any valid argument from either the devs or players in support of a two&nbsp;handed weapon, the evidence is there plain to see in the threads listed above that the Paladin community requested a 1HS epic. Historical weapon choice and art design are non starters here I'm sorry.</DIV></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Obviously it is up to the devs/design team what to do about it, but the issue here is pretty undeniable. If the epic 2.0 is also a 2HS it will be a huge blow to the Paladin class, and a very clear message to a class already struggling to find a place or job in Everquest that their wider issues are not going to be addressed.</DIV>
